  stimulus_text = 'The author of the passage suggests that “every person has a personal history,” and that “personal histories intersect.”  This intersection of histories can lead to a rich understanding of the complexities of the human experience. What is the most likely reason why the author of the passage emphasizes that "every person has a personal history"? Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
